British Museum. A vellum manuscript, in folio, con- sisting of 318 leaves, and containing various matters relating to the possessione and privileges of the monas· tery. What renders it of especial interest to us is that it is written throughout by the ex—abbot Thomas Burton's own hand. The writing is clearly to be recognized as his, though it has changed from the character exhibited in both the Phillipps and the Egerton MSS. Its con- tenta are as follow :- .
